<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-10 offset-md-1">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h2 class="text-center">NestJS Authentication Concepts Demo</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="lead text-center">
                    This application demonstrates different authentication concepts in a NestJS app.
                </p>
                
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <div class="card mb-4 auth-feature-card">
                            <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                                <h3 class="mb-0">Basic Authentication</h3>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <p>Demonstration of Basic Authentication with password hashing.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Username/password authentication using HTTP headers</li>
                                    <li>Password hashing with bcrypt</li>
                                    <li>Implementation using NestJS Guards</li>
                                    <li>Secure password storage</li>
                                </ul>
                                <div class="d-grid gap-2">
                                    <a href="/auth/basic" class="btn btn-primary">Try Basic Authentication</a>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <div class="card mb-4 auth-feature-card">
                            <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
                                <h3 class="mb-0">Digest Authentication</h3>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <p>Demonstration of Digest Authentication with nonce-based challenge-response.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Challenge-response authentication mechanism</li>
                                    <li>Nonce-based security to prevent replay attacks</li>
                                    <li>No plaintext password transmission</li>
                                    <li>MD5 hashing for response verification</li>
                                </ul>
                                <div class="d-grid gap-2">
                                    <a href="/auth/digest" class="btn btn-success">Try Digest Authentication</a>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <div class="card mb-4 auth-feature-card">
                            <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
                                <h3 class="mb-0">Session Authentication</h3>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <p>Demonstration of server-side session authentication with Redis.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Form-based authentication with modern UI</li>
                                    <li>Server-side session storage with Redis</li>
                                    <li>Flash messages for user feedback</li>
                                    <li>Multi-Factor Authentication support</li>
                                    <li>Stateful session management</li>
                                </ul>
                                <div class="d-grid gap-2">
                                    <a href="/auth/session/login" class="btn btn-info">Try Session Authentication</a>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="mt-4">
                    <h4>Coming Soon</h4>
                    <p>The following authentication methods will be implemented in future updates:</p>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="card mb-3 auth-feature-card">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">JWT Authentication</h5>
                                    <p class="card-text">Token-based authentication using JSON Web Tokens.</p>
                                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm" disabled>Coming Soon</button>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="card mb-3 auth-feature-card">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">OAuth 2.0 / OIDC</h5>
                                    <p class="card-text">Authentication using third-party identity providers.</p>
                                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm" disabled>Coming Soon</button>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="mt-4">
                    <h4>API Endpoints</h4>
                    <p>The following API endpoints are available for testing:</p>
                    <div class="table-responsive">
                        <table class="table table-striped">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Endpoint</th>
                                    <th>Method</th>
                                    <th>Authentication</th>
                                    <th>Description</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><code>/</code></td>
                                    <td>GET</td>
                                    <td>None</td>
                                    <td>Home page (this page)</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><code>/auth/basic</code></td>
                                    <td>GET</td>
                                    <td>Basic Auth</td>
                                    <td>Protected endpoint using Basic Authentication</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><code>/auth/digest</code></td>
                                    <td>GET</td>
                                    <td>Digest Auth</td>
                                    <td>Protected endpoint using Digest Authentication</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="mt-4">
                    <h4>Testing Authentication Endpoints</h4>
                    
                    <h5>Basic Authentication</h5>
                    <p>You can test the Basic Authentication endpoint using curl:</p>
                    <div class="bg-light p-3 rounded">
                        <pre>curl -v -u admin:secret http://localhost:3000/auth/basic</pre>
                    </div>
                    
                    <h5 class="mt-3">Digest Authentication</h5>
                    <p>Testing Digest Authentication requires multiple steps:</p>
                    <div class="bg-light p-3 rounded">
                        <pre>curl -v --digest -u admin:secret http://localhost:3000/auth/digest</pre>
                    </div>
                    <p class="mt-2"><small>Note: The <code>--digest</code> flag tells curl to handle the challenge-response mechanism automatically.</small></p>
                    
                    <p class="mt-2">Default credentials for all authentication methods:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Username: <code>admin</code></li>
                        <li>Password: <code>secret</code></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="mt-4">
                    <h4>Debug Tools</h4>
                    <p>Development-only tools for debugging and inspection:</p>
                    <div class="bg-light p-3 rounded">
                        <a href="/debug-tools" class="btn btn-outline-danger">Access Debug Tools</a>
                    </div>
                    <p class="mt-2"><small>Warning: These tools expose sensitive information and should only be used during development.</small></p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card-footer text-muted">
                <p class="mb-0 text-center">This is an educational demo. <strong>Do not use in production</strong> without proper security review.</p>
